modules.description: Parses and serializes Ethernet packets using Cstruct buffers, supporting protocol pretty-printing and size calculations. It handles decoding from and encoding into raw byte buffers, with error handling for invalid data. The module works with protocol identifiers and structured Ethernet packet data.

Provides functions to manage network connections, including writing and listening for packets, disconnecting, and retrieving MAC and MTU information. Operates on custom types `t` representing network interfaces and `error` for error handling. Used to send and receive network data, monitor interface statistics, and control device connections.

Handles Ethernet frame parsing and construction, including checksum validation and header extraction. Operates on raw byte sequences and structured Ethernet addresses. Used to process incoming network traffic and prepare outgoing packets for transmission.

Provides functions to write Ethernet frames with source and destination MAC addresses, handle input demultiplexing for ARP, IPv4, and IPv6, and manage disconnection. Operates on MAC addresses, packet protocols, and Cstruct buffers. Used to construct and route network traffic within an Ethernet interface.
